      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Let the user know that a team member from the clinic will give them a call back.\n\nIf {{callback_number}} is not empty:\n  Say something like: \"I'll make sure someone from the clinic reaches out to you at {{callback_number}}. They'll be able to help you with everything we discussed. Does that number still work?\"\n\nIf {{callback_number}} is empty:\n  Say something like: \"I'll make sure someone from the clinic gives you a call back on this number. They'll be able to help you with everything we discussed. Sound good?\"\n\nIf the user asks when:\n- If {{is_open}} is \"Yes\" and {{can_schedule_same_day}} is \"Yes\":\n  \"You should hear from us soon.\"\n- If {{is_open}} is \"No\" and {{can_schedule_same_day}} is \"Yes\":\n  \"The office opens at {{next_open}}, so you should hear from us soon.\"\n- If {{is_open}} is \"Yes\" and {{can_schedule_same_day}} is \"No\":\n  \"The office is wrapping up for the day, so you'll likely hear from us on {{next_available_for_reviewing}}.\"\n- If {{is_open}} is \"No\" and {{can_schedule_same_day}} is \"No\":\n  \"The office is currently closed, so you should hear from us on {{next_available_for_reviewing}}.\"\n\nIf the user asks who will call:\n\"It'll be one of our front desk team members — they'll have the notes from our conversation so you won't have to repeat anything.\"\n\nIf the user says that's NOT a good number or wants to use a different one:\n\"No problem — what's the best number to reach you?\"\nCollect the number, read it back, and confirm."
      }
    },
    {
