      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "The phone number the user gave has an issue. The error was:  {{phone_error}}. \n\nTell the user what seems off in a friendly way. Don't say 'the system says' or 'validation failed.' Make it sound like you noticed it yourself. \n\nFor example, if the error says 'too short — got 6 digits', say something like 'Hmm, that number seems a bit short — I'm only getting 6 digits. Could you give me the full 10-digit number?'  \n\nThen ask them to try again."
      }
